oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Maj. Gen. Robert L. Bullard, Mary Pickford, and Maj. Gen. George H. Harries
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Maj. Gen. Robert L. Bullard, movie star Mary Pickford, and Maj. Gen. George H. Harries (L to R). Incription on reverse reads"Him with the tinware is Geo. H. Harries." PhotographerAlbert R. Dupont (N.J.). Photograph is from a scrapbook with items about Harries. Harries' foreign medals were probably the result of his work repatriating prisoners of war after the war ended. Albert Dupont was the son of photographer Aime Dupont. He was also a Sgt. in HQ Co., 311th Inf. Regt., 78th Div.
